sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Pipeline
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Operator as Feast Operator<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant K8s as Kubernetes<br/>Resource Manager
    participant Online as Feature Server<br/>(Online Store)<br/>6566/6567 TCP
    participant Offline as Offline Store<br/>8815/8816 TCP
    participant Registry as Registry Server<br/>6570/6571 TCP gRPC
    participant CronJob as CronJob<br/>(ose-cli)
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP TLS
    participant UI as UI Server<br/>8888/8443 TCP
    participant ExtDB as External DB<br/>(PostgreSQL/Redis)
    participant MLApp as ML Application

    Note over User,K8s: Flow 1: FeatureStore Deployment
    User->>K8sAPI: Create FeatureStore CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (FeatureStore)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Services,<br/>ConfigMaps, PVCs, RBAC,<br/>CronJobs, Routes<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    K8sAPI->>K8s: Schedule & create resources

    Note over MLApp,ExtDB: Flow 2: Feature Serving (Online)
    MLApp->>Online: GET/POST features<br/>80/TCP or 443/TCP<br/>HTTP/HTTPS<br/>Auth: None / K8s RBAC / OIDC
    Online->>Registry: Fetch feature metadata<br/>gRPC 80/443<br/>TLS (if configured)
    Online->>ExtDB: Query backend store<br/>Auth: Secret-based

    Note over CronJob,ExtDB: Flow 3: CronJob Materialization
    CronJob->>Online: kubectl exec<br/>feast apply + materialize<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount (CronJob Role)
    Online->>ExtDB: Write materialized features<br/>Auth: Secret-based

    Note over User,UI: Flow 4: UI Access (OpenShift)
    User->>Route: Browse UI<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (edge/reencrypt)
    Route->>UI: Forward request<br/>8888/TCP or 8443/TCP<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
